<%# Right-aligned per-day relevance summary for a date header: a saved (♥) count,
    shown only when > 0 — so the date itself stays cleanly left-aligned with no
    sometimes-there icon. The count is adjusted by the save toggles within the day
    (day-summary controller, which lives on the day CONTAINER so those toggles
    bubble to it). %>
<% saved_count = events.count { |event| event_saved?(event) } %>
<div class="day-summary" aria-hidden="true">
  <span class="day-summary__count day-summary__count--saved" data-day-summary-target="saved" <%= 'hidden' unless saved_count.positive? %>><%= saved_count %></span>
</div>
